<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB03162</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROVIDING FOR EMERGENCY POWERS TO THE PRESIDENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF THE PHILIPPINES TO ADDRESS THE TRANSPORTATION CRISIS IN METRO MANILA</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : The Traffic Crisis Act Of Metro Manila 2016</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Grants emergency powers to the President of the Republic of the Philippines, giving him the authority to formulate and immediately implement, without hindrance and at shortest possible time, long-term solutions and remedial measures in solving the traffic problem that greatly impedes economic growth and makes life harder for the working class Filipino.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>TAMBUNTING, GUS S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-08-22</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Economic</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Bravo (M.) (026 2016-09-26)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Scheduled for meeting/hearing on 2017-05-10</b><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp2. Approved by the Committee on Appropriations on 2017-05-10</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Substitute Bill to House Bill Nos. 3, 38, 554, 1315, 1666, 3048, 3162, 3314, 3442, 3617, 3712, 3716, 4334, 4699 and HR No. 119 was approved with amendments.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB06425</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON TRANSPORTATION ON 2016-08-30</td></tr></table>